a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2023
a-size-base 3: I give my dogs a dental stick most every day, so we were happy to try out a bag of these dental rings.  The dogs really liked these and were able to devour them pretty quickly.  They did take slightly longer to chew than a normal dental stick, however.  The ingredients are not super alarming, though I don't think they are quite as good as our usual brand.  If you have a dog over 50 pounds, these are pretty easy to serve.  However, you are supposed to give dogs under 50 pounds less than a full ring a day, and these are rather hard to break.  You may be able to cut them, but I didn't think to try that because I have large dogs, so I am not sure how well that would work.  Each ring is 112 kcals, which is slightly more than the kind we usually use, so I like to give these only occasionally.  The bag does list all of the important information I look for; ingredients, guaranteed analysis, calorie content, feeding guidelines and expiration date. The dogs did not have any adverse reactions to these dental rings.  Though I don't feel this is the healthiest option out there, the dogs really loved them and the treats are not super unhealthy so I will probably keep these on as an occasional option to change up our daily routine.

a-size-base: Good chewies, but not long lasting
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2022
a-size-base 3: These are good chewy treats for dogs, as they have a decent list of ingredients and our dog didn't seem to mind eating it. He's not a picky eater, but there are some treat flavors he won't eat. It didn't take him long to  make this ring-shaped chew disappear, maybe a full minute if that.  The package may say it's for 'strong' chewers, but it sure doesn't seem like it. Maybe it's also based on dog size?  Our American Bulldog is a big chonker, and he chewed through this treat like it was nothing more than a marshmallow. Our little ten pound Min Pin mix took a lot longer to devour her piece, but she also didn't have any trouble biting through the treat. Price here on Amazon is certainly better than the box box pet stores, where these bags sell for at least twice the price (at least around here in NY well outside of the city). We've bought these rings before as our A.B. loved their puppy teething rings when he was that age. They also have a pumpkin flavor, but we've yet to come across ANY dog - be it our own or that of friends or family or even shelter pups - that like that flavor.  But the chicken flavored chewy rings, like these, are quickly taken after a cursory sniff. Because of the higher calorie content, our dog only gets one or two a week and only on the days when we know he will be getting extra exercise.
